<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link><description>World News Today: Read the latest world news headlines, Current International breaking news world wide. In depth analysis and top news headlines world wide.</description><language>en-gb</language><lastBuildDate>2026-07-20T20:52:56+05:30</lastBuildDate><atom:link type="application/rss+xml" rel="self" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/296589292.cms"/><copyright>Copyright:(C) Mon, 20 Jul 2026 20:52:56 IST Bennett Coleman &amp; Co. Ltd, http://in.indiatimes.com/policyterms/1554651.cms</copyright><docs>http://syndication.indiatimes.com/</docs><image><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><url>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/507610.cms</url><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link></image><item><title><![CDATA[A floating 'igloo' research station has left France for Arctic, where it will drift with polar ice]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132515527.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A floating research station shaped like a giant aluminium igloo has left France on a two-year Arctic mission to study biodiversity and the effects of climate change. The station will drift with sea ice while an international team of scientists collects more than 10,000 samples despite extreme cold, months of darkness and the risk of polar bear encounters.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-floating-igloo-research-station-has-left-france-for-the-arctic-where-it-will-drift-with-polar-ice-to-study-climate-change-and-life-in-one-of-earths-harshest-environments/articleshow/132515527.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-floating-igloo-research-station-has-left-france-for-the-arctic-where-it-will-drift-with-polar-ice-to-study-climate-change-and-life-in-one-of-earths-harshest-environments/articleshow/132515527.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:07:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516203,imgsize-285590.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Xi's US trip appears on track even as Trump's election interference claims inject fresh strain]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132518428.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/xis-us-trip-appears-on-track-even-as-trumps-election-interference-claims-inject-fresh-strain/articleshow/132518428.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/xis-us-trip-appears-on-track-even-as-trumps-election-interference-claims-inject-fresh-strain/articleshow/132518428.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:29:41+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132518438,imgsize-83090.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nepal's Re 1 coin gets a makeover: Controversial Kalapani-Lipulekh-Limpiyadhura map removed]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132517585.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/nepals-re-1-coin-gets-a-makeover-controversial-kalapani-lipulekh-limpiyadhura-map-removed/articleshow/132517585.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/nepals-re-1-coin-gets-a-makeover-controversial-kalapani-lipulekh-limpiyadhura-map-removed/articleshow/132517585.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:56:46+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132518047,imgsize-117920.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Archaeologists uncover 7,000-year-old fish traps that rewrite the story of life before farming in Scandinavia]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132518057.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/archaeologists-uncover-7000-year-old-fish-traps-that-rewrite-the-story-of-life-before-farming-in-scandinavia/articleshow/132518057.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/archaeologists-uncover-7000-year-old-fish-traps-that-rewrite-the-story-of-life-before-farming-in-scandinavia/articleshow/132518057.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:03:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132518107,imgsize-190770.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[California city manager arrested over alleged yacht burglary weeks after taking office]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132517503.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/california-city-manager-arrested-over-alleged-yacht-burglary-weeks-after-taking-office/articleshow/132517503.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/california-city-manager-arrested-over-alleged-yacht-burglary-weeks-after-taking-office/articleshow/132517503.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:52:08+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517589,imgsize-715647.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists marked this coral reef as dead in the 1960s; underwater drones found it alive...]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516959.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[After being presumed extinct for sixty years, a remarkable coral reef off West Africa has been rediscovered, thriving with an array of fish and coral species. This vibrant mesophotic coral ecosystem thrives in low-light environments beneath the ocean's surface. Researchers speculate that similar hidden reefs could exist along the West African coastline, providing valuable insights into the evolutionary history of the region's marine life and past environmental changes.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-marked-this-west-african-coral-reef-as-probably-dead-in-the-1960s-underwater-drones-found-it-alive-more-than-50-metres-below-the-sea/articleshow/132516959.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-marked-this-west-african-coral-reef-as-probably-dead-in-the-1960s-underwater-drones-found-it-alive-more-than-50-metres-below-the-sea/articleshow/132516959.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:49:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517609,imgsize-239610.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[FedEx CEO Raj Subramaniam grabbed the opportunity that his roommate rejected: He can't come but can I send my resume?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132517128.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/fedex-ceo-raj-subramaniam-grabbed-the-opportunity-that-his-roommate-rejected-he-cant-come-but-can-i-send-my-resume/articleshow/132517128.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/fedex-ceo-raj-subramaniam-grabbed-the-opportunity-that-his-roommate-rejected-he-cant-come-but-can-i-send-my-resume/articleshow/132517128.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:12:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517203,imgsize-523467.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Illinois farmers are making up to $200,000 a year without growing more crops as solar companies offer long-term leases worth up to $2,000 per acre]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516820.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/illinois-farmers-are-making-up-to-200000-a-year-without-growing-more-crops-as-solar-companies-offer-long-term-leases-worth-up-to-2000-per-acre/articleshow/132516820.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/illinois-farmers-are-making-up-to-200000-a-year-without-growing-more-crops-as-solar-companies-offer-long-term-leases-worth-up-to-2000-per-acre/articleshow/132516820.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:03:38+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517034,imgsize-1530920.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hunters carried trout past waterfalls into fishless Norwegian mountain lakes 7,000 years ago]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132515296.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a remarkable feat 7,000 years ago, ancient hunter-gatherers transformed Norwegian mountain lakes by introducing brown trout. Archaeologists discovered remnants of intricate fish traps from 5000 BC, highlighting how these early communities intentionally manipulated their ecosystems for sustainable food resources. They even transported live fish through rugged landscapes, paving the way for the fisheries we know today, where anglers still catch their ancient descendants.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/hunter-gatherers-carried-trout-past-waterfalls-into-fishless-norwegian-mountain-lakes-7000-years-ago-their-descendants-are-still-caught-there-today/articleshow/132515296.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/hunter-gatherers-carried-trout-past-waterfalls-into-fishless-norwegian-mountain-lakes-7000-years-ago-their-descendants-are-still-caught-there-today/articleshow/132515296.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:19:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516133,imgsize-247628.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A couple bought their dream home and got the keys, only to discover the property was a snake habitat after moving in]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516128.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Tyler and Lauren Bouldin bought an abandoned historic Pennsylvania home in 2020.  They discovered the neglected grounds had become a thriving habitat for various snakes.  The couple learned to manage the wildlife by making the property less attractive to them.  They safely captured and relocated snakes encountered near their home.  Five years later, the property is transformed into their dream family home.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/news/a-couple-bought-their-dream-home-and-got-the-keys-only-to-discover-the-property-was-a-snake-habitat-after-moving-in/articleshow/132516128.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/news/a-couple-bought-their-dream-home-and-got-the-keys-only-to-discover-the-property-was-a-snake-habitat-after-moving-in/articleshow/132516128.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:15:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Real Estate Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516184,imgsize-213502.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Saudi Arabia launches new one-year, multiple-entry Umrah visa with 90-day stay]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516106.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/saudi-arabia-launches-new-one-year-multiple-entry-umrah-visa-with-90-day-stay/articleshow/132516106.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/saudi-arabia-launches-new-one-year-multiple-entry-umrah-visa-with-90-day-stay/articleshow/132516106.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:21:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516266,imgsize-1575444.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian techie in Ohio dies from 'rare, life-threatening condition'; felt severe pain in left leg after dinner]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516124.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/indian-techie-in-ohio-dies-from-rare-life-threatening-condition-felt-severe-pain-in-left-leg-after-dinner/articleshow/132516124.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/indian-techie-in-ohio-dies-from-rare-life-threatening-condition-felt-severe-pain-in-left-leg-after-dinner/articleshow/132516124.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:09:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516152,imgsize-96182.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A 26-year-old quit corporate job in Chicago to be a seamstress for $19.25 an hour]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132510728.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Zoe De La Paz, 26, left her corporate engineering job in Chicago to work as a seamstress at Yellowstone National Park, turning a high-school hobby into a full-time career. After gaining experience through backstage jobs at music venues, she now repairs uniforms at Yellowstone while working towards her long-term goal of joining Broadway and film costume departments in New York City.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-26-year-old-quit-her-corporate-drafting-job-in-chicago-to-become-a-seamstress-at-yellowstone-for-19-25-an-hour-hoping-it-will-lead-to-broadway-and-film-work/articleshow/132510728.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-26-year-old-quit-her-corporate-drafting-job-in-chicago-to-become-a-seamstress-at-yellowstone-for-19-25-an-hour-hoping-it-will-lead-to-broadway-and-film-work/articleshow/132510728.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517040,imgsize-302134.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Florida turns restaurant waste into reefs; fish and dolphins rebound]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132512434.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Florida restored parts of the Gulf of Mexico by returning more than 500,000 tonnes of recycled oyster and clam shells to the sea between 2007 and 2024. The shells helped rebuild oyster reefs, improve water quality and support the return of fish, turtles and dolphins to levels not seen in over 25 years.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/florida-returned-half-a-million-oyster-shells-to-the-gulf-of-mexico-the-discarded-shells-became-new-reef-habitat-for-marine-life/articleshow/132512434.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/florida-returned-half-a-million-oyster-shells-to-the-gulf-of-mexico-the-discarded-shells-became-new-reef-habitat-for-marine-life/articleshow/132512434.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T17:58:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132513952,imgsize-448818.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Some species of mosquitoes in the UK spread avian malaria]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516580.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a landmark study, researchers have pinpointed certain mosquito species that spread avian malaria in the UK. Among twelve species analyzed, nine were found to harbor traces of this bird disease. Notably, the Ochlerotatus detritus mosquito is suspected to transmit Plasmodium vaughani to blackbirds, with additional species identified as potential carriers for parasites that threaten various native birds.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/mosquito-species-in-the-uk-are-potential-carriers-of-avian-malaria-new-study-finds/articleshow/132516580.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/mosquito-species-in-the-uk-are-potential-carriers-of-avian-malaria-new-study-finds/articleshow/132516580.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:48:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516671,imgsize-102486.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Weaponisation of water': Pakistan seeks Canada's help to revive Indus Waters Treaty with India]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132515471.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pakistan's Deputy Prime Minister Ishaq Dar requested Canadian support for the Indus Waters Treaty.  He stated India suspended the agreement, adding a new dynamic to security.  Dar urged India to end water weaponization and uphold international law.  India maintains its position remains in abeyance due to terrorism.  Pakistan views the Indus as a lifeline and will defend its sovereignty.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/weaponisation-of-water-pakistan-seeks-canadas-help-to-revive-indus-waters-treaty-with-india/articleshow/132515471.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/weaponisation-of-water-pakistan-seeks-canadas-help-to-revive-indus-waters-treaty-with-india/articleshow/132515471.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T17:53:24+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclo